### Create event
POST http://localhost:8080/api/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Backend Engineering Workshop",
  "city": "Warsaw",
  "category": "education",
  "startsAt": "2026-09-01T10:00:00+02:00",
  "totalCapacity": 10
}

### Get event
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events/{{eventId}}

### Create reservation
POST http://localhost:8080/api/events/{{eventId}}/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerFullName": "Jan Kowalski",
  "customerEmail": "jan.kowalski@example.com"
}

### Confirm reservation
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/confirm

### Cancel reservation
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/cancel

### Get reservation
GET http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}

### Async confirm with approved payment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/confirm-async?paymentScenario=APPROVED

### Async confirm with slow payment provider, expected PAYMENT_TIMEOUT after ~2s
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/confirm-async?paymentScenario=SLOW

### Async confirm with failing payment provider, expected PAYMENT_TIMEOUT fallback
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/confirm-async?paymentScenario=FAILING

### Async confirm with declined payment, expected 400 and reservation remains PENDING
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reservations/{{reservationId}}/confirm-async?paymentScenario=DECLINED

### Stage 4: transactional self-invocation pitfall
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/transactional/self-invocation

### Stage 4: lazy loading broken endpoint
# Replace reservationId with an existing reservation id.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/reservations/{{reservationId}}/lazy-broken

### Stage 4: lazy loading fixed by transaction boundary
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/reservations/{{reservationId}}/lazy-fixed-transaction

### Stage 4: lazy loading fixed by DTO projection
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/reservations/{{reservationId}}/lazy-fixed-projection

### Stage 4: lazy loading fixed by fetch join
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/reservations/{{reservationId}}/lazy-fixed-fetch-join

### Stage 4: lazy loading fixed by entity graph
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/reservations/{{reservationId}}/lazy-fixed-entity-graph

### Stage 4: AOP through this, aspect bypassed
POST http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/aop/through-this?input=spring

### Stage 4: AOP through proxy, aspect executed
POST http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/aop/through-proxy?input=spring

### Stage 4: bean lifecycle
GET http://localhost:8080/api/spring-pitfalls/bean-lifecycle

### Stage 5 — event search optimized by composite index
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?city=Warsaw&from=2026-06-01T00:00:00Z&category=music

### Stage 5 — organization reservations, offset pagination
GET http://localhost:8080/api/organizations/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations?status=CONFIRMED&page=0&size=50

### Stage 5 — customer reservations, offset pagination
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations?page=0&size=50

### Stage 5 — customer reservations, keyset pagination
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations/keyset?size=50

### Stage 5 — event stats
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/stats

### Stage 5 — N+1 intentionally naive
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations/n-plus-one

### Stage 5 — N+1 fixed by fetch join
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations/fetch-join

### Stage 5 — N+1 fixed by EntityGraph
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/reservations/entity-graph

### Stage 5 — EXPLAIN ANALYZE for event search, PostgreSQL only
GET http://localhost:8080/api/performance/explain/event-search?city=Warsaw&category=music&from=2026-06-01T00:00:00Z

### Stage 6: short reservation burst
POST http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/events/{{eventId}}/short-reservations?requests=1000

### Stage 6: parallel reservation burst
POST http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/events/{{eventId}}/parallel-reservations?requests=1000&threads=64

### Stage 6: organization report profiling
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/organizations/{{organizationId}}/report

### Stage 6: allocation pressure
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/allocations?objects=500000

### Stage 6: lock contention
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/lock-contention?threads=64&incrementsPerThread=100000

### Stage 6: CPU thread pool experiment
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/thread-pool?threads=8&tasks=500&workloadType=CPU

### Stage 6: IO thread pool experiment
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/thread-pool?threads=64&tasks=500&workloadType=IO

### Stage 6: BigDecimal allocation scenario
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profiling/big-decimal-allocation?iterations=500000
